    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix undefined behavior in SRS rank indicator computation\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_srs_ri_computation` function in the gNB scheduler incorrectly handled rank indicator calculation for SRS measurements. When the channel condition counting logic resulted in a non-positive value, the function failed to explicitly set the `ul_ri` output parameter, leaving it uninitialized. This led to unpredictable MIMO layer selection during PUSCH scheduling, causing potential data transmission failures or suboptimal link performance.\n\nThe issue manifested when UE SRS measurements indicated poor channel conditions across most PRGs, triggering the undefined code path. Affected systems included 2x2 MIMO configurations where SRS-based rank adaptation was enabled.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_srs.c`: Added explicit initialization of `*ul_ri = 0` for non-positive condition count cases, ensuring deterministic rank indicator output.\n"
}